title: Co-Director, Web Developer
description: Penn Labs is a University-sponsored group of developers, designers, and intrapreneurs who make software products for students at Penn. As director, I meet often with administrators and the Undergraduate Assembly (UA) to find needs in the Penn community and structure our project development to meet those needs. I also oversee our five teams to ensure all memebers are engaged and development is going smoothly. I'm currently also building Penn Basics, a centralized source of dining, study, laundry, and events information on campus.

title: VP Marketing, Webmaster
description: YouthHack is an international organization dedicated to building student entrepreneurs. I lead the Core Team in all marketing initiatives for events, partnerships, and programs. I also consult student-run ventures within our Ventures Accelerator program.

title: Project Consultant
description: MUSE, or the Marketing Undergraduate Student Establishment, is a club at Wharton dedicated to marketing-oriented event planning and consulting. Through MUSE, I developed go-to-market strategies, market research, and brand positioning for our clients.
